00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:10,080
 love, to be that church of hope that wraps its arms around those who are in need.

35
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:13,200
 This reminds me of a dream I had a few weeks ago.

36
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:17,560
 And in this dream, I was shown a scripture but without the words.

37
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:22,000
 So I knew this was a scripture, and I sensed God was saying in the scripture, "The first

38
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,920
 part you're doing really well, but the second part you're not doing well."

39
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:29,880
 So the whole day, and this never came up, you know, Matthew 22.

40
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:34,080
 So the whole day I was thinking and agonizing, and I came to worship.

41
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:35,800
 Usually God speaks to me in worship.

42
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:39,360
 So I came to worship, I was agonizing, "God, you've got to tell me, because if you don't

43
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,760
 tell me, then I can't repent."

44
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:41,760
 Nothing.

45
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:47,060
 Then after that, the whole day I was really like, "God, you need to tell me," you know.

46
00:02:47,060 --> 00:02:52,160
 And just before I went into a prayer meeting with some ladies, God began to reveal it.

47
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:59,840
 I think the suspense had to come for me to really weep for what God showed me.

48
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:03,960
 I then realized the second dream I'd had the same night was connected to the first.

49
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:08,280
 Because in the second dream, God had shown me someone who was in need.

50
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:11,960
 God had shown me somebody who needed hospital fees.

51
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:16,320
 God had shown me the need of this person, but I had not called that person, I had not

52
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:20,920
 provided for that person, and I had certainly not prayed for that person.

53
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:25,440
 God called me out and weeping, I told the people I was in the prayer meeting with, and

54
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:29,840
 we're all weeping and repenting, because every single one of them realized they had done

55
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,840
 the same.

56
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:37,440
 In the busyness of life, especially in Hong Kong, we can sometimes be so too busy to even

57
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,320
 look at the need around us.

58
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:47,280
 But I believe God has even created today, this Sunday, for us to pause a little bit

59
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:50,740
 and see the need around us.

60
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:54,160
 The last two weeks, Pastor Andrew has really been unpacking what justice is, and it's been

61
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:55,160
 amazing.

62
00:03:55,160 --> 00:04:00,880
 I'm not theologian, but today I'm going to unpack as well what branches of hope needs,

63
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:04,800
 and we believe all of us need, and that is love.

64
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:09,440
 In the first week, Pastor Andrew spoke about four key relationships.

65
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:13,200
 Us with God, and it seems from the dream I was doing well with that.

66
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:16,780
 Us with ourselves, I'm not sure about that because it wasn't revealed.

67
00:04:16,780 --> 00:04:21,360
 But us with others, I wasn't doing so well there, and then us with creation.

68
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:27,280
 Today we're going to focus on us with others, and in particular with branches of hope.

69
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:32,160
 Last week, Pastor Andrew mentioned that you cannot call yourself a Christian and remain

70
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:36,220
 distant to the injustice in the society around you.

71
00:04:36,220 --> 00:04:41,640
 When the plight of the asylum seekers and refugees in our church became so glaring,

72
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:43,340
 we could not keep quiet.

73
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:44,880
 We had to step forward.

74
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,200
 We had to see.

75
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:52,960
 We had to weep and begin to speak about what people were experiencing in this church.

76
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:59,800
 And not only that, branches of hope and the ministry of Arise was birthed from this need.

77
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:05,880
 And year after year, the voice of branches of hope has become louder and louder and louder

78
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:11,400
 because of the love, the prayers, and the generosity of the people in this room.

79
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:17,480
 The love, prayer, and giving of you has changed many lives and given hope to those in a dire

80
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:20,600
 situation.

81
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:24,880
 We also learned last week that the local church, the body of Christ, is always called to walk

82
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:29,440
 towards the community and love it.

83
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:34,520
 But in order for us to know what this love is really about, we're going to unpack a little

84
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:41,000
 bit of the Greek word for love in Matthew 22, verse 37 to 40.

85
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:45,360
 There are actually four Greek words I want to speak about, and the last one is what we

86
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,480
 see in Matthew 22.

87
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:50,940
 So philia love, this is a brotherly love.

88
00:05:50,940 --> 00:05:55,920
 This is an affectionate kind of love based on feelings and proximity.

89
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:58,160
 And then there's storge love, which is the family love.

90
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:03,000
 This is a bond created in being a family.

91
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:07,100
 When I look at storge, nowadays I've got a teenage daughter, and she seems to be leaning

92
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:11,040
 more on philia than storge, but that's okay.

93
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,140
 Then there's eros love.

94
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:16,080
 This is a love normally based on feelings and passion for each other.

95
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:18,700
 But today we want to focus on agape love.

96
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:22,280
 This is a sacrificial and unconditional love.

97
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:29,240
 While philia, storge, and eros are basically primarily a love of emotion, agape is not

98
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:35,320
 primarily an act of feelings, though it can be involved, but a love of devotion and acts

99
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:37,840
 that flow from God.

100
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:43,720
 This kind of love in Matthew 22, verse 37 to 40 is agape.

101
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:48,440
 Today we're going to also look at some scriptures related to agape, because in the New Testament,

102
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:51,520
 agape is mentioned over 100 times.

103
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:53,120
 That means it's very important.

104
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:57,200
 But today we want to look at some of those scriptures, not all 100, but some of those

105
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:03,840
 scriptures in order for us to see what the definition of agape really is.

106
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:08,040
 So turn with me to 1 John 3, verse 16 to 18.

107
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:12,540
 We know what real love is, because Jesus gave up his life for us.

108
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:16,980
 So we also ought to give up our lives for our brothers and sisters.

109
00:07:16,980 --> 00:07:22,560
 If someone has enough money to live well and sees a brother or sister in need but shows

110
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:27,440
 no compassion, how can God's love be in that person?

111
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:30,840
 Dear children, let's not merely say that we love each other.

112
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,760
 Let us show the truth by our actions.

113
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:37,360
 This is a real scripture, everyone.

114
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:42,360
 Maybe sometimes you're like me, and I sometimes skip through some of these scriptures and

115
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:49,640
 think, "Oh, I know what God wants me to give," until God calls me out in a dream and says,

116
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:50,640
 "Pause.

117
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:55,680
 You need to look around you and really see."

118
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,460
 It is selfless, unconditional, and it flows from God.

119
00:07:58,460 --> 00:08:00,520
 This is what we see from the scripture.

120
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,420
 It flows from God.

121
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:03,420
 It is selfless.

122
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:04,960
 It's looking at others.

123
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:10,760
 It is purposely looking for the need around us.

124
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:14,400
 God gave us his best, so we should also give our best.

125
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:20,220
 The love that God has poured in us during when we got saved is the same love he feels

126
00:08:20,220 --> 00:08:23,040
 we should pour into other people.

127
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:26,800
 The primary way we share is action-oriented.

128
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:32,600
 The primary way God showed his love was action by sending Jesus Christ.

129
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:38,080
 The primary way he wants us to show our love is an action-oriented thing, by giving our

130
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:44,120
 time, by giving our resources, by giving our energy, by giving our prayer, and yes, by

131
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:48,920
 even giving financially to those who are in need.

132
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:53,440
 It is expressed through actions and deeds and not just words like we've just said.

133
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,840
 Turn with me to James 2, verse 8 and 18.

134
00:08:55,840 --> 00:09:02,120
 It says, "Yes, indeed, it is good when you obey the royal law as found in the scriptures.

135
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:04,120
 Love your neighbor as yourself."

136
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:09,840
 Now someone may argue some people have faith, others have good deeds, but I say, "How can

137
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,960
 you show me your faith if you don't have good deeds?"

138
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:16,560
 I will show you my faith by my deeds.

139
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,160
 Agape is a doing word.

140
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,120
 Well, the other three are primarily nouns.

141
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:25,120
 If you don't remember, you can go back to your English.

142
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:28,320
 Agape is a doing word.

143
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:32,980
 To truly live out the word agape, we must partner our words with our actions.

144
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:36,580
 We must also move forward with our deeds.

145
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:38,400
 It is also a work of the Holy Spirit.

146
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:45,640
 Recently, we were having the Holy Spirit series and Galatians 5, verse 22 to 23 came up, but

147
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:52,640
 the Holy Spirit produces this kind of fruit in our lives, love, joy, peace, patience,

148
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:57,880
 kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, and self-control.

149
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:01,400
 There is no law against these things.

150
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:06,400
 When we were learning about the fruit of the Spirit, the word love in that verse is agape.

151
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:09,920
 We cannot agape in and of ourselves.

152
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:15,440
 We need the Holy Spirit to help us to agape because it is countercultural to agape.

153
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:22,680
 Where a culture says we give to get something back, agape says I would disadvantage myself

154
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:25,720
 for the good of others.

155
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:31,480
 I recently came across a friend sent me the story of Yvonne Roberts, the Welsh revivalist.

156
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:38,120
 He was a revivalist, a leading part of a revival in Wales in 1904 to 1905.

157
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:43,240
 Through the work of the Holy Spirit, there was a lot of prayer during that revival.

158
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:47,200
 There was a lot of people getting saved during that revival.

159
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,940
 The prisons were emptied during that revival.

160
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:56,280
 But the most amazing thing was there were no more people in need in Wales during that

161
00:10:56,280 --> 00:11:01,720
 time, during that revival because everybody was led by the Holy Spirit to begin to go

162
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:07,700
 to the churches and begin to give whatever the Holy Spirit was compelling them to give.

163
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:16,600
 What a beautiful view of how God wants us to meet each other's needs.

164
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:29,960
 "It should flow from us to others just as it flowed from us to God, from God to us.

165
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:34,800
 It should flow from us to others just as it flowed from God to us."

166
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:40,720
 In John 13, 34 to 35, "So now I am giving you a new commandment.

167
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:43,680
 Love each other just as I have loved you.

168
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,600
 You should love each other.

169
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:50,360
 Your love for one another will prove to the world that you're my disciples."

170
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:54,880
 And the love should not stop with us because there are other people who need to see this

171
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,040
 love.

172
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:59,400
 God pours it into us so we can pour into other people.

173
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:02,740
 In Branches of Hope, we serve some people who don't know God.

174
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:07,680
 And the only way they will want to know God is when they see the love flowing from us

175
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:11,720
 to them.

176
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:18,160
 So with these four verses, we will go to an extended definition that I came up with.

177
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:25,880
 And the new definition for agape is, "It is an unconditional, sacrificial love that flows

178
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:31,640
 from God through the Holy Spirit and leads us to acts of selfless love for others."

179
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:37,140
 Essentially, it is what Andrew spoke about and described in the first week, being willing

180
00:12:37,140 --> 00:12:42,600
 to disadvantage ourselves for the advantage of our community.

181
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:48,320
 I truly believe that if everybody gave what God asked us to give, there would be no lack

182
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,840
 in the church of God.

183
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,800
 There would be no lack in the kingdom of God.

184
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:57,440
 This is a beautiful picture of how God has equipped each and every one of us to meet

185
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,440
 each other's needs.

186
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:03,320
 It's like a God community where no one lacks anything, whether it is prayer, whether it

187
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:09,520
 is fellowship, whether it is resources or anything, because at any given time, we probably

188
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:10,760
 need one of those.

189
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:14,240
 And at any given time, we probably can give one of those.

190
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:20,080
 Allow me to share some of the acts of love that have been expressed to some of our clients

191
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,600
 through Branches of Hope recently.

192
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:29,120
 Our stop program recently helped a man called Saul, a father of three from Indonesia, who

193
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:33,880
 had sold his most prized possession, a rice field, to cover a broker's fee who had promised

194
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:38,680
 him a high-paying dishwashing job in Hong Kong.

195
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:44,080
 When he arrived in Hong Kong, his dreams were shattered when he discovered the job was a

196
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,080
 lie.

197
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:50,160
 His tourist visa expired, and his limited English made it difficult for him to navigate

198
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:53,120
 the immigration requirements to go back home.

199
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:58,240
 Thankfully, Stop's Indonesian caseworker, Dedi, accompanied him from the immigration

200
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:01,680
 office to the shelter and through the courtroom.

201
00:14:01,680 --> 00:14:08,000
 Dedi interpreted and guided him through the complex administrative and legal processes.

202
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:14,960
 Saul was ultimately given a non-custodial sentence in order to return to Indonesia.

203
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:20,280
 Stop bought his ticket and helped him secure business startup funding from the International

204
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:23,280
 Organization for Migration.

205
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:30,800
 At the airport, Saul was overjoyed and grasped Dedi's hands tightly, his eyes shining with

206
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:31,800
 gratitude.

207
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:38,400
 The assistance Saul received not only sent him back home to safety, but it gave him a

208
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:41,320
 new lease of life.

209
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:45,920
 You might have also read the story of Lisa, an asylum seeker from Russia, in the Branches

210
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:49,480
 of Hope article published on World Refugee Day.

211
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:55,640
 Lisa is one of the 200,000 people in Hong Kong that Andrew spoke about last week who

212
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:59,120
 live in a 100-square-foot home.

213
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:03,360
 She lives with her son, James, in a subdivided flat in Hong Kong.

214
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:08,120
 As she waits for her case to go through the lengthy process, she cannot work and has to

215
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:11,960
 survive on the limited government allowance.

